# Maven & Dependencies

## Parent POM (`pom.xml` at root)

- Inherits from `spring-boot-starter-parent` 3.3.5.
- Declares `<modules>` for all child modules.
- All shared dependency versions go in `<dependencyManagement>`.
- `maven-compiler-plugin` configured in `<pluginManagement>` with Lombok annotation processor.

## Module POMs

- Parent: `quantum-edu-be-parent`.
- Declare only the dependencies that module actually uses — no version tags (managed by parent).
- Lombok: add `<dependency>` with `<scope>provided</scope>` (version from parent BOM).
- `spring-boot-maven-plugin` is ONLY in the `app` module POM — never in library modules.

## Adding a New Module

1. Create `modules/<name>/pom.xml` with parent reference.
2. Add `<module>modules/<name></module>` to the parent POM.
3. Add the module artifact to parent `<dependencyManagement>`.
4. Add it as a dependency in `app/pom.xml`.

## Adding a New Dependency

- If it may be reused across modules, add it to parent `<dependencyManagement>` with a version.
- In the module POM, declare just `groupId + artifactId` (no version).
- Always check if Spring Boot BOM already manages the version before adding one.
